<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-07-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-07-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="258" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d258">
                        <head>No. 254.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Messrs. <persName type="from">Cushing
                                    and McKenney</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Portland, Me.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-07-03"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 3, 1886</date>.
                                [Received July—.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Our schooner City Point seized in Shelburne, Nova Scotia, for taking in
                            water and allowing men ashore before reporting. Please give
                            instructions.</p>
                        <closer><signed>CUSHING &amp; McKENNEY.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>